    "summary": "Gleb Vdovin obtained MSc in Optical Engineering  in 1986 from ITMO University, USSR, and  PhD in 1996 from TU Delft, the Netherlands. He is a founder of  OKO Technologies, adaptive optics developer and supplier since 1997. As technical consultant Gleb has participated in 4 startups. In 1997 he received Rudolph Kingslake Medal and Prize form SPIE.  A number of technical articles  published by Dr. G. Vdovin  received  citation index of higher than  100.\n\nSpecialties:  simulation, design, development and production of custom opto-electronic and information processing systems. Applications include  metrology, imaging, spectral instruments, medical optics, communications, and laser beam control.",
